二、指定教科書及參考資料 Textbooks and Reference(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)


●指定教科書 Required TextsBusiness analysis and valuation. Krishna G.Palepu, Paul M.Healy, and Erik Peek (2013, Third Edition).Published by CENGAGE Learning.
		●參考書資料暨網路資源 Reference Books and Online Resources董珮真、蔡順達，台商在中國的經營策略，臺北市進出口商業同業公會，2007。麥瑞台，大陸台商的經營策略，成陽出版2006年。吳迎春、李明軒、盧智芳等著，台商徵霸全球，臺北市：天下雜誌。顧淑馨譯，大前研一著，全球五臺大未來，臺北市：臺北培生教育出版，2005。


三、教學目標 Objectives


This course includes business practice and management issues covered from the global region economics as a whole, and a general description of individual countries with an in-depth analysis, and uses an easy way to introduce complicated issues. This course also analyzes the global regional economic and trade information practice; furthermore, it gathers the latest case of Taiwanese businessman and companies in the global region after each section.　


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall DescriptionCOURSE DESCRIPTION    This course will deal with effective global business practice and decision making through cross-cultural business and management cases. It will be an in-depth study of the various types of business operation and management. Students will be exposed to the tenets of performance evaluation. In addition, they will learn about the control of operations, capital budgeting, and effective management of assets. This course is the foundation course for all future advanced global business management studies.    Inasmuch as this is a master level seminar, traditional textbook assignments will not be emphasized. Each student will be expected to make meaningful, worthwhile contributions to every assigned area. This course requires prior preparation, or the student will be overwhelmed. Furthermore, the course is very intense and will involve assignments to be worked after class. Some of these assignments are done at the time of the class instead of in advance because the ability to work as a team with your fellow students is an important part of the learning process. 


●分週敘述 Weekly Schedule





